        content: `AI in Today’s Indian Marketing Field: Transforming Strategies with Data-Driven Precision:\nIn India’s dynamic marketing landscape, Artificial Intelligence (AI) is revolutionizing how businesses connect with consumers. With the Indian digital advertising market projected to reach ₹51,110 crore by 2025, AI is a game-changer for brands striving to stand out.\n\nAI impact is most evident in personalized marketing and predictive analytics. Indian startups like Zomato leverage AI for hyper-local targeting, while e-commerce giants like Flipkart use AI-powered chatbots to handle 70% of customer queries, significantly cutting operational costs.\n\nFor SMEs, AI levels the playing field by enabling precise ad targeting on platforms like Google Ads, achieving measurable ROI improvements. AI is no longer just a trend but a strategic imperative for businesses nationwide.\n\nBy:\nDr. M.N. Manik,\nProfessor and Dean Academic, Chetan Business School MBA, Hubli`
